<span class="kw">PLAN 1: SALE BUDGET PLAN</span> <span class="cm">(replaces V-0063 Excel, 685 MB)</span><br>
"How much will each store sell?" → <span class="fm">BGT_SALE_QTY, BGT_SALE_VAL</span><br>
Source: Snowflake FACT_SALE_GENCOLOR + FACT_DEMAND_FORECAST<br>
Grain: Store × MajCat × Month<br><br>

<span class="kw">PLAN 2: FIXTURE & DENSITY PLAN</span> <span class="cm">(replaces V-0081 Excel)</span><br>
"How much display stock should each store have?" → <span class="fm">BGT_DISP_QTY, ACC_DENSITY</span><br>
Depends on: Plan 1 output<br>
Grain: Store × MajCat × Month<br><br>

<span class="kw">PLAN 3: WEEKLY DISAGGREGATION</span> <span class="cm">(replaces manual Excel split)</span><br>
"Split monthly → 48 weekly buckets" → <span class="fm">QTY_SALE_QTY, QTY_DISP_QTY</span><br>
Depends on: Plan 1 + Plan 2 output<br>
Grain: Store × MajCat × 48 Weeks<br><br>

<span class="kw">PLAN 4: TRANSFER IN PLAN (TRF)</span><br>
"How much stock should each store receive?" → <span class="fm">TRF_IN_PLAN</span><br>
Depends on: Plan 3 output (QTY_SALE_QTY, QTY_DISP_QTY)<br>
Grain: Store × MajCat × Week
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="algo-block">
<span class="kw">PLAN 5: PURCHASE PLAN (PP)</span><br>
"How much should each DC purchase?" → <span class="fm">PURCHASE_PLAN</span><br>
Depends on: Plan 4 output (TRF_IN_PLAN)<br>
Grain: RDC × MajCat × Week<br><br>

<span class="kw">PLAN 6: SUB-LEVEL TRANSFER IN PLAN</span><br>
"Break TRF by MVGR/Size/Segment/Vendor" → <span class="fm">SUB_LEVEL_TRF_PLAN</span><br>
Uses: CONT_PCT + level-specific stock<br>
Grain: Store × MajCat × SubValue × Week<br><br>

<span class="kw">PLAN 7: SUB-LEVEL PURCHASE PLAN</span><br>
"Break PP by MVGR/Size/Segment/Vendor" → <span class="fm">SUB_LEVEL_PP_PLAN</span><br>
Depends on: Plan 6 output<br>
Grain: RDC × MajCat × SubValue × Week<br><br>

<span class="kw">PLAN 8: ARTICLE ALLOCATION (ARS)</span> <span class="cm">(external Azure API)</span><br>
"Which specific articles + sizes to send?" → <span class="fm">Delivery Orders → SAP</span><br>
Reads: BGT_DISP_QTY from Supabase<br>
5 engines: Budget Cascade → Scoring → Filling → Size → DO
                    </div>
