<!-- ═══ TAB: PLAN 1 ═══ -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tabP1">
    <div class="card shadow-sm plan-card p1 mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0" style="color:#8B5CF6;"><i class="bi bi-coin me-2"></i>Plan 1: Sale Budget Plan</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> "How much will each store sell per major category per month?"<br>
            <strong>Replaces:</strong> V-0063 Excel (685 MB, 1006 columns, operated manually by Mehfuj)<br>
            <strong>Data Source:</strong> Snowflake V2RETAIL.GOLD → SQL Server staging → Algorithm → SALE_BUDGET_PLAN</p>

            <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Algorithm (3 methods)</h6>
            <div class="algo-block">
<span class="kw">METHOD 1 — LYSP Growth</span> (V-0063 logic):<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">BGT_SALE_QTY</span> = LYSP_QTY × (1 + growth_rate) × fill_rate_adj × (1 + festival_adj)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;Growth: YoY from Snowflake actuals (store×cat, category, store level)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;Fill Rate: If FR &lt; 70%: increase | If FR &gt; 130%: decrease | Dampened at 50%<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;Min 7 days cover enforced<br><br>

<span class="kw">METHOD 2 — ML Forecast</span> (from Snowflake FACT_DEMAND_FORECAST):<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">BGT_SALE_QTY</span> = STORE_FORECAST <span class="cm">(pre-computed ensemble)</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;4 methods: WMA, Exponential Smoothing, Seasonal, Regression<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;Weighted by MAPE accuracy, 34 months historical data<br><br>

<span class="kw">METHOD 3 — Hybrid</span> (default):<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;IF ML exists: <span class="fm">BGT</span> = 60% × ML + 40% × LYSP-based<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;ELSE: use LYSP-based or contribution % distribution<br><br>

<span class="kw">VALUE:</span> <span class="fm">BGT_SALE_VAL</span> = BGT_SALE_QTY × ASP (avg selling price from LYSP or MRP)
            </div>

            <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Snowflake Tables Used</h6>
            <table class="table table-sm table-bordered mb-0">
                <thead class="table-dark"><tr><th>Table</th><th>Rows</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td><code>FACT_SALE_GENCOLOR</code></td><td>12.5M</td><td>Actual sales + LYSP at Store × GenColor × Week</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>FACT_DEMAND_FORECAST</code></td><td>106K</td><td>ML ensemble forecasts per Store × MajCat × Month</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>FACT_CONT_PCT_STORE</code></td><td>168K</td><td>Store contribution %, closing stock, PSF, GM%</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>DIM_ARTICLE_GENCOLOR</code></td><td>1.16M</td><td>GenColor → Major Category, Division, MRP</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><code>DIM_STORE</code></td><td>315</td><td>Store master: zone, region, state, area, cohort</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ TAB: PLAN 2 ═══ -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tabP2">
    <div class="card shadow-sm plan-card p2 mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0" style="color:#E67E22;"><i class="bi bi-grid-3x3-gap me-2"></i>Plan 2: Fixture & Density Plan</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> "How much display stock should each store have per category?"<br>
            <strong>Replaces:</strong> V-0081 Excel (371 columns) — State model, ROI scoring, density output<br>
            <strong>Depends on:</strong> Plan 1 (SALE_BUDGET_PLAN) + Snowflake staging data</p>

            <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Algorithm</h6>
            <div class="algo-block">
<span class="kw">DISPLAY QUANTITY:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">BGT_DISP_QTY</span> = BGT_SALE_QTY × Display% <span class="cm">(APP: 28%, GM: 45%, Other: 35%)</span><br><br>

<span class="kw">DENSITY:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">ACC_DENSITY</span> = MIN(article_count, display_qty) <span class="cm">(articles per fixture slot)</span><br><br>

<span class="kw">FIXTURES:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">FIX_COUNT</span> = ROUND(display_qty / density)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">AREA_SQFT</span> = fix_count × 4 sqft <span class="cm">(per fixture)</span><br><br>

<span class="kw">ROI METRICS:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">GP_PSF</span> = Gross Profit per Square Foot <span class="cm">(for prioritization)</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">SALES_PSF</span> = Sale Value / Store Area<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">STR%</span> = Sell-Through Rate = Sale / (Sale + Stock)
            </div>

            <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Output: FIXTURE_DENSITY_PLAN</h6>
            <p>Store × MajCat × Month with BGT_DISP_QTY, BGT_DISP_VAL, ACC_DENSITY, FIX_COUNT, AREA_SQFT, GP_PSF, SALES_PSF</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ TAB: PLAN 3 ═══ -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tabP3">
    <div class="card shadow-sm plan-card p3 mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0 text-info"><i class="bi bi-calendar3 me-2"></i>Plan 3: Weekly Disaggregation</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Split monthly budgets into 48 weekly columns to feed TRF & PP plans<br>
            <strong>Replaces:</strong> Manual Excel monthly-to-weekly split<br>
            <strong>Depends on:</strong> Plan 1 (SALE_BUDGET_PLAN) + Plan 2 (FIXTURE_DENSITY_PLAN) + WEEK_CALENDAR</p>

            <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Algorithm</h6>
            <div class="algo-block">
<span class="kw">INPUT:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;SALE_BUDGET_PLAN: monthly BGT_SALE_QTY per Store × MajCat<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;FIXTURE_DENSITY_PLAN: monthly BGT_DISP_QTY per Store × MajCat<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;WEEK_CALENDAR: maps months to week numbers (WK-1..WK-48)<br><br>

<span class="kw">DISAGGREGATION:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">Sale Qty:</span> Monthly qty ÷ weeks_in_month = equal per-week amount<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e.g. Apr budget 1000 qty, 4 weeks in Apr → WK-1=250, WK-2=250...<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">Display Qty:</span> Same value repeated for all weeks in month<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="cm">(display is stock level, not flow — stays constant within month)</span><br><br>

<span class="kw">OUTPUT:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">QTY_SALE_QTY</span>: ST-CD, MAJ-CAT, WK-1, WK-2, ... WK-48 <span class="cm">(TRUNCATE + INSERT)</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">QTY_DISP_QTY</span>: ST-CD, MAJ-CAT, WK-1, WK-2, ... WK-48 <span class="cm">(TRUNCATE + INSERT)</span><br><br>

<span class="kw">CRITICAL:</span> This REPLACES existing QTY_SALE_QTY and QTY_DISP_QTY data.<br>
After disagg, run Plan 4 (TRF) → Plan 5 (PP) to regenerate all downstream plans.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ TAB: PLANS 4-5 ═══ -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tabP4P5">
    <div class="card shadow-sm plan-card p4 mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0 text-success"><i class="bi bi-arrow-left-right me-2"></i>Plan 4: Transfer In Plan + Plan 5: Purchase Plan</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <p>These are the <strong>existing core plans</strong> already in production. See <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Info")">App Info & Formulas</a> for complete algorithm documentation.</p>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h6 class="fw-bold text-success">Plan 4: TRF Algorithm (week chaining)</h6>
                    <div class="algo-block">
<span class="kw">FOR EACH</span> Store × MajCat × Week:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;WK1: <span class="fm">OP_STK</span> = STORE_STOCK<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">SHRINKAGE</span> = OP × 8% × SSN_FACTOR<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">NET_CF</span> = MAX(OP - SHRINKAGE, 0)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">MBQ</span> = DISP + Next_Week_SALE<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">TRF_IN</span> = MAX(MBQ + SALE - NET_CF, 0)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">CL_STK</span> → next week OP_STK<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;SP: <code>SP_GENERATE_TRF_IN_PLAN</code>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h6 class="fw-bold" style="color:#8E44AD;">Plan 5: PP Algorithm (DC chaining)</h6>
                    <div class="algo-block">
<span class="kw">FOR EACH</span> RDC × MajCat × Week:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">TRF_OUT</span> = SUM(TRF_IN by RDC)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">DC_MBQ</span> = MIN(next 4wk TRF_OUT, SALE)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">GRT_CONS</span> = MIN of 4 constraints<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">PUR_Q</span> = MAX(MBQ + TRF_OUT - NET_CF, 0)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="fm">DC_CL_STK</span> → next week<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;SP: <code>SP_GENERATE_PURCHASE_PLAN</code>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="alert alert-info py-2 mt-2 mb-0"><i class="bi bi-info-circle me-1"></i>Full formula reference with all 30+ TRF columns and 40+ PP columns available at <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Info")">App Info & Formulas → TRF Algorithm / PP Algorithm tabs</a></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ TAB: PLANS 6-7 ═══ -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tabP6P7">
    <div class="card shadow-sm plan-card p6 mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0" style="color:#D97706;"><i class="bi bi-layers me-2"></i>Plans 6-7: Sub-Level TRF + PP</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <p><strong>Same algorithm</strong> as Plans 4-5 but at finer granularity with 4 dimensions:</p>
            <div class="row g-3 mb-3">
                <div class="col-md-3"><div class="card bg-light p-2 text-center"><strong>MVGR</strong><br><small>Macro MVGR Matrix</small></div></div>
                <div class="col-md-3"><div class="card bg-light p-2 text-center"><strong>Size</strong><br><small>SZ</small></div></div>
                <div class="col-md-3"><div class="card bg-light p-2 text-center"><strong>Segment</strong><br><small>SEG</small></div></div>
                <div class="col-md-3"><div class="card bg-light p-2 text-center"><strong>Vendor</strong><br><small>M_VND_CD</small></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="algo-block">
<span class="kw">KEY DIFFERENCES:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;• Sale Qty × <span class="fm">CONT_PCT</span> from contribution table<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;• Display Qty × <span class="fm">CONT_PCT</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;• Store stock from <span class="fm">SUB_ST_STK_{level}</span> (not STORE_STOCK)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;• DC stock from <span class="fm">SUB_DC_STK_{level}</span> (not DC_STOCK)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;• Granularity: Store × MajCat × <span class="fm">SUB_VALUE</span> × Week<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;• No bin rounding (raw quantities)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;• PP: GRT_CONS_Q = 0 (simplified)
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2">Full documentation at <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Info")">App Info → Sub-Level Plans tab</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ TAB: PLAN 8 ═══ -->
<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tabP8">
    <div class="card shadow-sm plan-card p8 mb-3">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-robot me-2"></i>Plan 8: ARS — Article Allocation</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> "Which specific articles + sizes to send to each store?"<br>
            <strong>System:</strong> ARS (Auto Replenishment System) — Python FastAPI on Azure App Service<br>
            <strong>API:</strong> <code>ars-v2retail-api.azurewebsites.net</code> | <strong>Performance:</strong> &lt;6 min for 1M store-article pairs</p>

            <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">5-Engine Pipeline</h6>
            <table class="table table-sm table-bordered mb-0">
                <thead class="table-dark"><tr><th>Engine</th><th>Name</th><th>What It Does</th></tr></thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td><span class="badge bg-primary">1</span></td><td>Budget Cascade</td><td>Reads <code>co_budget_store_major_category</code> from Supabase → MBQ per store × MAJCAT</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><span class="badge" style="background:#E67E22;">2</span></td><td>Article Scoring</td><td>Scores every DC article against every store using 14 weighted factors</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><span class="badge bg-success">3</span></td><td>Greedy Filler</td><td>Fills option slots with highest-scoring articles, equitable distribution (lowest fill-rate first)</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><span class="badge" style="background:#8B5CF6;">4</span></td><td>Size Allocator</td><td>Breaks options into size-level quantities using <code>co_budget_company_major_category_size</code></td></tr>
                    <tr><td><span class="badge bg-danger">5</span></td><td>DO Generator</td><td>Compiles delivery orders with full article details → SAP RFC → Store delivery</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Tech Stack</h6>
            <p>Python FastAPI | Azure App Service | Azure SQL + Supabase (387K budget rows) | Snowflake (analytics) | JWT Auth + RBAC + RLS</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

